timeline.bodyText:
We need to check here for null like we are doing everywhere else to see if the values of zoom controls and zoom enabled in the developer provided config are null, then we need to use the values from the default config.
@arislomovic You also need to specify a default value of true for these controls in the msal_default_config.json. See this file: https://github.com/AzureAD/microsoft-authentication-library-for-android/blob/dev/msal/src/main/res/raw/msal_default_config.json
so that when the developer doesn't specify a value for these fields in their config, then we can use the default true from the msal default config

